{
  "stem": "802.6",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I was-- I got two-- I got two MAs and a PhD in comparative literature.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and I've been teaching since that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I teach, among other things, the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Virtually always, I taught the Holocaust at the graduate school, City University Graduate Center.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I taught it also at NYU-- Literary Responses to the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And now, when I teach, I always incorporate, whenever I can, the Holocaust, you know, and especially if it's modern literature.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I teach English essentially now, with an accent.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, well, I may have indicated to you before that I have a kind of double vision, kind of bifocal vision.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I see things-- I'm a woman, and I see my experiences through a girl's eyes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, at the same time, I am a woman and an older woman.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so my interpretation of what happened to us is-- is obviously different from that of the child who was there, OK?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In that sense, it's-- it's bifocal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I see things with, you know, with-- as I said, with a child's eyes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I interpret them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, of course, I was interpreting things, then, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I don't remember precisely.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I just remember some of my feelings.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, my work essentially focuses on the literature during the Holocaust, not after the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And while some people think that the literature that was written during the Holocaust is better, because it reflects the immediacy of experience-- while this is true, on the other hand, recalling the past and examining it, and arriving at-- at an understanding as an adult, is also important-- if I'm making myself clear.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I don't-- 'cause there's an awful lot among, you know, scholars, this-- a bit of tension about this.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
